Since the AWEs have large electrical double-layer capacitors, pulse voltages will cause great non-Faradic currents. This great current will damage the power supply circuits. Hence, pulse currents instead of pulse voltages are chosen as the implementation measures for the low-load state. By changing the pulse width or duty ratio (namely Ton/TP\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
